subSection.paragraph:
The detoxification of phytoalexins by phytopathogenic fungi 
in planta
decreases the concentrations of essential defenses and facilitates successful microbial invasion. Importantly, it has been shown in several instances that fungal plant pathogens detoxify cruciferous phytoalexins using different reactions and that the 
type
of reaction (e.g. oxidation, reduction, hydrolysis) or pathways depend on both the fungal species and the chemical structure of the phytoalexin (
Pedras and Ahiahonu, 2005
; 
Pedras and Abdoli, 2017a
). For example, the cruciferous phytoalexin brassinin (
2
) is detoxified by phytopathogenic fungi to indolyl-3-methanamine (
4
) (in 

Alternaria brassicicola
(Schwein.) Wiltshire

) and indole-3-carboxaldehyde (
3
) (in 

Leptosphaeria maculans
(Desm.) Ces. et Not.

, asexual stage 

Phoma lingam
(Tode ex Fr.) Desm.

), whereas rapalexin 
A
(
1
) is not transformed by either pathogen (
Fig. 2
) (
Pedras and Sarma-Mamillapalle, 2012
; 
Pedras and Abdoli, 2017b
).

